> Although shepherd's pie was originally created as a "clean out the refrigerator" dish to use up leftovers, it has morphed into a warm and comforting classic to enjoy any night of the week. After all, what's not to love about the combination of hearty ground beef, caramelized onions, and a crunchy potato crust?

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 420 degrees. Toss @baby carrots{8%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until starting to brown, about ~{20%minutes}.

Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Place in a large #pot{} of salted water. Bring to a boil and cook until fork tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Drain and return to pot.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Mince @garlic{2%clove}. Strip @thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves off stems. Discard stems.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and thyme. Cook until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside. Add another drizzle of @olive oil{} and onions to pan. Cook until softened, about ~{6%minutes}. Add garlic and @water{1/4%cup}.

Sprinkle @flour{1%tablespoon} over and stir ~{1%minute}. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/2%cup}, and @peas{4%ounce}. Stir until sauce thickens, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add beef and stir to combine. Use a fork or #potato masher{} to mash potatoes with @milk{1/4%cup} and @butter{1%tablespoon} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer beef mixture to a medium #baking dish{}. Spread mashed potatoes over top. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, and bake until melted and bubbly, about ~{5%minutes}. Serve with roasted carrots on the side.